    <!-- Company Story Section -->
    <section class="py-5" aria-labelledby="story-heading" itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization">
      <div class="container py-5">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
          <div class="col-lg-8 text-center" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h2 id="story-heading" class="display-6 fw-bold mb-4">Our Story</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row g-5 align-items-center">
          <div class="col-lg-6" data-animate="fade-up">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1553877522-43269d4ea984?w=600&h=400&fit=crop" alt="Startup team brainstorming with sticky notes on a whiteboard" class="img-fluid rounded-4 shadow" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-6" data-animate="fade-up" data-animate-delay="100">
            <p class="lead mb-4" itemprop="description">In 2019, three engineers at a fast-growing startup hit a wall. Their team had outgrown spreadsheets, but every project management tool they tried felt like it was built for a different era.</p>
            <p class="text-muted mb-4">Too many clicks. Too many features they did not need. Too much friction between having an idea and actually executing on it.</p>
            <p class="text-muted mb-4">So they built Launchpad - first as an internal tool, then as a product. The goal was simple: create something they actually wanted to use. Something fast, flexible, and focused.</p>
            <p class="text-muted">Today, over 5,000 teams trust Launchpad to manage their projects. And we are still building with the same philosophy: great tools should get out of your way so you can do great work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission & Values Section -->
